notes: The model failed to identify the critical access control vulnerability in the MigrateTroveZap contract. The function _0x390062 allows an attacker to specify an arbitrary victim's address as the _0xac561e parameter. Since the victim may have previously approved the MigrateTroveZap contract (a common pattern for 'zap' contracts), the attacker can trigger actions on behalf of the victim and receive the resulting tokens (line 64). The model incorrectly labeled the contract as safe.
